author: jta
msg: Derby web site reorg:
1) Changed the blue navigation menu to beige using the "Lenya using pelt"
colors in the skinconf.xml, but set the Lenya subheading and published
values to "#E5E4D9" and "#FFFFFF", respectively.
2) Added new "Quick Start" tab and page.
3) Added new "Downloads" tab that links to existing content and also features
the latest official release in the nav menu. The downloads overview page still
needs to be rewritten.
4) Renamed "Manuals" tab to "Documentation". Moved the doc links from nav menu
to the body of the index page so pages can be opened in a new browser window
using forrest's class="fork".
5) Combined the "Papers" and "Integrate" tabs into one "Resources" tab.
6) Renamed logo_contest.html to logo.html in preparation to move
http://wiki.apache.org/db-derby/DerbyGraphicsAndLogo to this space.
Since the tabs.xml and site.xml config files were modified substantially,
every page on the web site gets rebuilt.
